      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk man. i was just looking at some photos of the deep field from james webb and it just hit me. everything we do, every single thing... it's all just noise. the universe is so massive and indifferent, and in a few billion years the sun dies and everything just goes dark. what is even the point of trying to build anything or be anything if none of it actually matters in the long run? it feels like we're all just screaming into a void that doesn't even hear us.",
